claim: Cell- and egg-based flu vaccines have the potential to develop mutations during production, which may reduce their effectiveness.
explanation: A table of solicited adverse event rates (any, moderate, severe) in subjects receiving a study vaccine, with footnotes describing severity grading and study populations. The table presents safety/reactogenicity data (percentages of adverse events by severity) for vaccine study participants. It does not address manufacturing methods, viral mutations during production, or vaccine effectiveness. Note: The visible portion of the table only includes adverse event data and footnotes; no information on production methods or antigenic changes is present.
